    "causal_summary": "sk-interface-design vendored from Anthropic's frontend-design skill (Apache-2.0) to give the framework reusable, advisor-routable guidance for distinctive UI design. It owns aesthetic direction (palette, typography, layout, motion, copy) and a brainstorm-critique-build process that avoids templated AI defaults; sk-code owns the implementation. Lean house-template SKILL.md routes to the full principles in references/design_principles.md. A mixed-license merge from the MIT ui-ux-pro-max repo added a quality-floor reference, a critique-against pattern inventory, nine design data CSVs under assets/data/, and an optional zero-dependency BM25 search (scripts/design_search.py); the design-system generator and persistence were deliberately excluded to protect the anti-default philosophy. The skill ships a feature_catalog/ and a manual_testing_playbook/ for sk-doc alignment.",
